DOC.brief_summary: This study aims to investigate the effect of Acu-TENS on forced expiratory volume in one second (FEV1), a test of pulmonary function used to assess airway resistance, during sub-maximal treadmill exercise in healthy subjects.
DOC.brief_title: Effect of Acu-Transcutaneous Electrical Nerve Stimulation (Acu-TENS) on Post-exercise Expiratory Flow Volume in Healthy Subjects
DOC.criteria: With normal health Suffered from respiratory, cardiovascular, musculoskeletal, neurological or endocrine disorders No allergic to gel
